<br>
Mercenaries are a fairly complete class. However, this is true only because Mercenaries mature with Realm Ranks. The increased desirability of Mercenaries in RvR groups has more to do with access to powerful cheap RA's than because of the class's function. Continuing to have to rely on these cheap, very effective RA's to define a role for ourselves is an undesired situation. Mercenaries would like unique effective tools that allows us to fulfil our &quot;positional fighter&quot; role regardless of Realm Rank or balancing actions to RA's.<br>
The only changes to Mercenaries in 1.65 came in the form of tweaks to the Crush style list. The change to Bludgeon was well received. Many Mercenaries do not like the changes made to Concussion &amp; Bone Crusher.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>CONCERNS</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>The Role of the Light Tank.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> In 1.62, Light Tanks were defined as positional fighters, or assist tanks. In this regard, Mercenaries suffer an identity crisis since very few of our tools are tailored to achieve this. Our Dual Wield spec line appears to be nothing more than another base style list. Given the Mercenaries weapon spec, they can swap any particular positional from the base style lists with the positionals from the Dual Wield style list, and gain no benefit or penalty for doing so.  A 44 Thrust spec Armsman is as much a &quot;positional fighter&quot; as a 50 DW spec Mercenary.  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Pure Tank Realm Abilities.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> It is access to these Realm Abilities (RA's) that is giving Mercenaries a rise in popularity. The Prevent Flight RA combined with our ability to Dual Wield is unmatched in Albion. Our access to Determination, especially above level 3, further compounds the issue by ensuring we're able to be in position to Prevent Flight over the course of an entire battle. If at any time these RA's are decreased in effectiveness, so will the Mercenary's role in RvR.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>SPECLINE ISSUES</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">Dual Wield:</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
<br>
- This specline should reflect our new role as positional fighters or assist tanks above and beyond any base spec line, yet does not.<br>
<br>
- One of our positionals, Flank, suffers serious penalties due to its lack of To-Hit bonus. In PvE, the only encounters challenging enough for a full group or a larger force, will be very purple. Such high level monsters renders a no To-Hit style like Flank and its followup, ineffective. In RvR this is also seen when fighting Keep Lords. Against other players, the fluidity of a battle prevents the constant re-use of a side positional. With Flank's lack of consistancy, it is more efficient to rely on some other style to hit for less damage, more often.<br>
<br>
- The Damage vs. Endurance cost for Misty Gloom arguably makes this the worst style in this spec line.<br>
<br>
- Dark Tendrils was changed in 1.62 to be a Parry reactional. Given the popularity of the Reflection-&gt;Hypnotic Darkness chain for the Stun effect and Dual Shadows for the Bleed Effect, Dark Tendrils is rarely used.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">Shield:</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> <br>
<br>
- Mercenaries who choose a hybrid configuration including shield spec are penalized for doing so. The interface to change from weapon to shield is time consuming and disliked. While a shield is equipped, the Mercenary is penalized by having unused points invested in the Dual Wield spec as well as being unable to use Dual Wield styles. Mercenaries have very little reason to wear shields since the defensive playstyle is better suited to other classes.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>CLASS ISSUES</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">Charge:</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
<br>
- Since the introduction of the Charge ability to Light Tanks, better forms of Endurance Regeneration as well as Endurance Potions have been introduced to the game. The charge ability is now nearly redundant since groups with a source of Endurance Regeneration nearly always travel with sprint active, which is the equivalent of an unlimited Charge ability. For the Mercenary in a group without Endurance Regeneration, the ability is still rendered useless if the opponent is regenerating endurance via potion or buff/chant/song. The opponent can continue sprinting long after the 10 seconds from Charge have elapsed and not worry about Mercenaries catching up since Charge offers no speed increase.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">Dirty Tricks:</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
<br>
- This ability is highly situational as well as completely ineffective against 17 of 39 classes in the game.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>OTHER ISSUES</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
- Void needs to be replaced by a worthwhile RA<br>
- Mercenaries question why we do not gain access to the Avoid Pain RA.<br>
- It has been confirmed that Evade I does not scale equally compared to higher levels of Evade when enhanced by buffs.<br>
- When dual wielding a 1h spear type weapon, the Mercenary holds a weapon in the left hand as well as the spear.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>DOCUMENTATION ISSUES</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
- When Dirty Tricks is activated, the Mercenary doesn't get any message.  It should state something along the lines of &quot;You pick up an handful of dirt!&quot;<br>
- When Dirty Tricks procs, there is no message.  It should state something along the lines of &quot;You throw dirt at XXX's eyes!&quot;. <p>Kerrec Snowmane<br>
